    "created_at": "2016-08-24T13:08:18Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-08-24T13:09:05Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "On second thought... this has the unfortunate and not very nice side-effect that our integer-percentage damage modifiers are now nowhere near precise enough.  We had previously worked around this for superweapons and other high-damage weapons by multiplying the damage falloff by 10 and dividing the base damage to compensate, but this is now going to be a problem everywhere.\n\nI now believe that this is the wrong solution that makes our problems worse instead of better.\n"
  },
