    "created_at": "2016-08-24T15:04:00Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-08-24T15:04:00Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Not really, unless you want to sweep it in with\n\n> Note: This will somewhat affect balancing,\n> ...\n> At least a certain amount of testing will have to go into this PR.\n\n(which I guess is valid enough).\n\nThe key point is that this PR only solves part of the problem, so I would very much prefer that we revert the numbers back to the values they had in the last N releases and then address all the problems together in next+1.  Otherwise we're going to lose another month or two on our already far-too-delayed next release, risk more balance regressions, and then need to repeat this all over again in the next cycle anyway.\n"
